<item>
            <title>[FLINK-20379] Update KafkaRecordDeserializationSchema to enable reuse of DeserializationSchema and KafkaDeserializationSchema</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-20379</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The new Kafka Connector defines its own deserialization schema and is incompatible with the existing library of deserializers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That means that users cannot use all of Flink&apos;s Formats (Avro, JSON, Csv, Protobuf, Confluent Schema Registry, ...) with the new Kafka Connector.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we should change the new Kafka Connector to use the existing Deserialization classes, so all formats can be used, and users can reuse their deserializer implementations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would also be good to use the existing KafkaDeserializationSchema. Otherwise all users need to migrate their sources again.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
